    |   |-- move.{c,h}             Move struct and execution
    |   |-- input.{c,h}            User input parsing
    |   |-- ai.{c,h}               Computer opponent
    |   |-- log.{c,h}              Move logging
    |   |-- undo.{c,h}             Undo functionality
    |   |-- board_bundle.{c,h}     Game state management
    |   |-- board_state.{c,h}      User interaction state
    |   |-- game_controller.{c,h}  Game flow coordination
    |   |-- save.{c,h}             Save/load game states
    |   |-- test_rulecheck.c       Rule validation tests
    |   |-- test_boarddisplay.c    Display tests
    |   |-- test_cpu_move.c        AI tests
    |   `-- gui/
    |       |-- gui.{c,h}          GTK app and window
    |       |-- render.{c,h}       Cairo drawing
    |       |-- color_gui.{c,h}    Color scheme
    |       `-- resources/         Piece images
    |-- bin/                       Built executable (after make)
    `-- doc/
        |-- Chess_UserManual.pdf   Application specification
        `-- Chess_SoftwareSpec.pdf Software architecture spec


----------------------------------------------------------------
7. FEEDBACK AND SUPPORT
----------------------------------------------------------------

This is the official release (V1.1) of Anteater Chess. All known issues from the alpha version have been resolved, including complete illegal move validation, multiple AI difficulties, and stable special-move handling.

For questions or feedback, contact the development team.
